The paper describes a ranking algorithm that uses pairwise comparisons between items, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The use of spectral methods and seriation suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), or information theory (cs.IT). The focus on ranking and comparisons makes cs.LG and cs.DS the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI and cs.SI, while cs.IT is less likely but still possible given the use of spectral methods.
